  <header>InspireSphere</header>

  <div class="story-container">
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1617054201806-bb457b2781f9?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1050&q=80" alt="Wheelchair Warrior" />
    
    <h1>Wheelchair Warrior</h1>
    <p>
      After a tragic accident left Aaron Fotheringham in a wheelchair at the age of eight, most people assumed he’d live a quiet life. But Aaron had other plans. Inspired by extreme sports, he decided to take his wheelchair to the skatepark—and redefine what was possible.
    </p>
    <p>
      Aaron became the pioneer of WCMX (Wheelchair Motocross), performing backflips, tricks, and stunts never seen before in the sport. Nicknamed the “Wheelz”, he has toured with Nitro Circus, amazed crowds worldwide, and shown millions that disabilities don’t define dreams. His courage inspires a new generation to rewrite their limits.
    </p>

